<p><br />
<b>Codependence</b> is a term which has been defined variously. In general, the codependent is understood to be a person who perpetuates the <a href="/wiki/Alcoholism" title="Alcoholism">alcohol</a> or <a href="/wiki/Drug_dependence" title="Drug dependence" class="mw-redirect">drug dependence</a> of someone close to them in a way that hampers recovery.<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> This can be done through direct control over the dependent, by making excuses for their dysfunctional behavior or relieving them of the consequences of the dependence. In an act called <a href="/wiki/Enabling" title="Enabling">enabling</a>, this can have negative social and health consequences for both parties.<sup id="cite_ref-addr_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-addr-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
